text: Shenzhou 12 was a Chinese spaceflight that launched on 17 June 2021. It was the seventh crewed Chinese spaceflight and the seventh crewed flight of the Shenzhou program. The spacecraft carried three members of the People's Liberation Army Astronaut Corps (PLAAC) on the first flight to the Tianhe core module. It is the first module of the Chinese space station Tiangong. ==References== Category:June 2021 events Category:Chinese spacecraft
title: Shenzhou 12
